{%- comment -%}
  Phase 3 — Audience personalization, single source of truth.

  How it works:
  1. This snippet sets `current_audience = 'generic'` SERVER-SIDE because
     Shopify Liquid has no native access to URL query strings (`request`
     exposes path, host, origin, locale, page_type — but no query params).
  2. <body> renders with class "audience-generic" baked in via Liquid.
  3. A tiny inline <script> at the top of <body> (in layout/theme.liquid)
     reads ?audience= from the CURRENT URL only, and swaps the body class
     to "audience-women" or "audience-men" if matched. No cookie. No
     persistence. Each page evaluates fresh.
  4. All variant-specific content (announcement bar copy, hero banner,
     subtitle, description, trust pills, FAQ, reviews, timeline copy,
     comparison rows, science lead, timer accent) is RENDERED THREE TIMES
     server-side, wrapped in `.aud-only-{generic|women|men}` containers.
     CSS in `assets/audience-variants.css` gates visibility based on the
     body class — only the matching variant is shown.

  Why pre-render all three rather than JS swap content: keeps Liquid
  single-source-of-truth (no JS-templated copy), avoids FOUC on copy
  swap, and makes Mike's Theme Customizer edits to any variant block
  just-work. Cost: ~3x markup on personalized blocks. Gzipped, this is
  a few KB at most — well under the budget for the conversion lift.

  Usage:
    {%- render 'audience-detect' -%}   <!-- once near top of layout/theme.liquid -->

  After render, the variable {{ current_audience }} is available for any
  Liquid that needs it, and CSS classes .aud-only-women / .aud-only-men
  / .aud-only-generic are honoured site-wide.
{%- endcomment -%}

{%- assign current_audience = 'generic' -%}
